    public interface ConfigurationManager

      • isAllowUnauthenticatedAccess

        boolean isAllowUnauthenticatedAccess(String contentId)
        Determines if the given content, identified by a user-generated contentId, has been configured to display content for unauthenticated users. For security and backwards compatibility purposes, implementations should use false as a default value in case a configuration is missing.
        Parameters:
        contentId - The id of the content in question. This id can be any non-blank string and gives developers the flexibility to define several content identifiers for the same portlet.
        Returns:
        true if the content identified by the given contentId can be displayed for unauthenticated users.

      • getStatisticsFilePath

        String getStatisticsFilePath()
        Path of the file containing statistics for statistics-portlet. This is is typically the output of the statistics-cli tool.
        Returns:
        the path where the statistics file is located.
